member.summary: Creates a new ASP.NET AJAX extender password strength cell.

member.name: P:FarPoint.Web.Spread.Extender.PasswordStrengthCellType.PreferredPasswordLength
member.summary: Gets or sets the ideal length of the password.
member.remarks: This property determines the preferred or ideal length of the password. Passwords could be less than this amount but do not reach the 100-percent calculation if less than this count. This is used to calculate 50-percent of the percentage strength of the password. Ideally, a password should be 20 characters in length to be a strong password.

member.name: P:FarPoint.Web.Spread.Extender.PasswordStrengthCellType.MinimumNumericCharacters
member.summary: Gets or sets the minimum number of numeric characters required for the password.
member.remarks: This property determines the minimum number of numeric characters required. If there are less than this property, then the password is not considered strong. If the number of characters is equal to or greater than this value, then this contributes 15-percent to the overall password strength.

member.name: P:FarPoint.Web.Spread.Extender.PasswordStrengthCellType.HelpHandleCssClass
member.summary: Gets or sets the CSS class used to display help for the password requirements.
member.remarks: This property determines the CSS class used to display the image for showing the password requirements to meet. This is provided so that the user can click on this image and get a display on what is required to make the password strong according to the current properties.

member.name: P:FarPoint.Web.Spread.Extender.PasswordStrengthCellType.HelpHandlePosition
member.summary: Gets or sets the position of where the help handle is displayed for the password.

member.name: P:FarPoint.Web.Spread.Extender.PasswordStrengthCellType.HelpStatusLabelID
member.summary: Gets or sets the identifier of the help status label for the password.

member.name: P:FarPoint.Web.Spread.Extender.PasswordStrengthCellType.MinimumSymbolCharacters
member.summary: Gets or sets the minimum number of symbol characters for a password to be considered strong.
member.remarks: This property determines the minimum number of symbol characters (e.g. ^,*, percent symbol, etc.) required for the password to be considered strong. If there are less than this property, then the password is not considered strong. If the number of characters is equal to or greater than this value, then this will contribute 15-percent to the overall password strength.

member.name: P:FarPoint.Web.Spread.Extender.PasswordStrengthCellType.RequiresUpperAndLowerCaseCharacters
member.summary: Gets or sets whether mixed case letters are required for a password to be considered strong.
member.remarks: This property determines if mixed case passwords are required to be considered strong. If true, then there must be at least one occurrence of mixed case (upper and lower) letters in the password to be considered strong. If there is, this will contribute 20-percent to the overall password strength percentage value.

member.name: P:FarPoint.Web.Spread.Extender.PasswordStrengthCellType.TextCssClass
member.summary: Gets or sets the CSS class to apply to the text of the editing control for a password.

member.name: P:FarPoint.Web.Spread.Extender.PasswordStrengthCellType.BarBorderCssClass
member.summary: Gets or sets the CSS class to apply to the bar border for a password.

member.name: P:FarPoint.Web.Spread.Extender.PasswordStrengthCellType.BarIndicatorCssClass
member.summary: Gets or sets the CSS class to apply to the bar indicator for a password.

member.name: P:FarPoint.Web.Spread.Extender.PasswordStrengthCellType.PrefixText
member.summary: Gets or sets the text prefixed to the password strength display value when using text display mode.

member.name: P:FarPoint.Web.Spread.Extender.PasswordStrengthCellType.DisplayPosition
member.summary: Gets or sets the display position for a password.

member.name: P:FarPoint.Web.Spread.Extender.PasswordStrengthCellType.StrengthIndicatorType
member.summary: Gets or sets the type of password strength indicator.
member.remarks: This property determines the visual display of the password strength. It is either a bar (as in a progress bar indicating percentage strength) or text (as in low, medium, high, or excellent).

member.name: P:FarPoint.Web.Spread.Extender.PasswordStrengthCellType.CalculationWeightings
member.summary: Gets or sets the calculation weightings of the password strength.
member.remarks: This property determines the calculation ratios or "weightings" used when calculating a passwords strength. The value must be a string with four elements separated by a semi-colons. The total of all four elements must equal one hundred percent. Default is "50;15;15;20" which represents ... Password Length Requirements : 50-percent ... Numerics Requirements : 15-percent ... Casing Requirements : 15-percent ... Symbol Character Requirements: 20-percent

member.name: P:FarPoint.Web.Spread.Extender.PasswordStrengthCellType.TextStrengthDescriptions
member.summary: Gets or sets the text strength descriptions for a password.
member.remarks: This property determines a string that specifies the string descriptions, delimited by semi-colons, for the password strength when using a textual display. An example of a string would be "None;Weak;Medium;Strong;Excellent"

member.name: P:FarPoint.Web.Spread.Extender.PasswordStrengthCellType.StrengthStyles
member.summary: Gets or sets the styles of the text strength descriptions for a password.
member.remarks: This property determines a string, delimited by semi-colons, that specifies the styles applicable to each string description for the password strength when using a textual display.

member.name: P:FarPoint.Web.Spread.Extender.PasswordStrengthCellType.MinimumLowerCaseCharacters
member.summary: Gets or sets the minimum number of lower case characters for a password to be considered strong.
member.remarks: If the property is true, then this property determines the minimum lower case characters that are required. The default value is 0 which means this property is not in effect and there is no minimum limit.

member.name: P:FarPoint.Web.Spread.Extender.PasswordStrengthCellType.MinimumUpperCaseCharacters
member.summary: Gets or sets the minimum number of upper case characters for a password to be considered strong.
member.remarks: If the property is true, then this property determines the minimum upper case characters that are required. The default value is 0 which means this property is not in effect and there is no minimum limit.
